title: Kate Middleton, Prince William and Prince Harry to attend world premiere of the latest Bond movie
text:
Tweet 
The latest Bond movie, Spectre, will have some special royal guests at its world premiere. 
The Duchess of Cambridge, née Kate Middleton, Prince William and Prince Harry are set to make their appearance at the Royal Albert Hall on Oct. 26, for the world’s first screening of the new James Bond movie. 
The Kensington Palace announced last week that the royal trio will be present at the event. 
“The Duke and Duchess and Prince Harry will attend the world premiere of #SPECTRE in aid of @thectbf on Oct 26,” the Palace tweeted on Sep. 16. The Duke and Duchess and Prince Harry will attend the world premiere of #SPECTRE in aid of @thectbf on Oct 26 pic.twitter.com/FnYmQ4MMsu 
— Kensington Palace (@KensingtonRoyal) September 16, 2015 
We’re definitely looking forward to see what gown the British royal mother-of-two will choose for this occasion. 
Kate, William and Harry are set to be present at the world premiere where they will meet the Spectre cast including Daniel Craig, Monica Bellucci, Lea Seydoux, Christoph Waltz, Ralph Fiennes, David Bautista, Naomie Harris and Ben Whishaw. 
Director Sam Mendez, as well as producers Barbara Broccoli and Michael G. Wilson will also hit the red carpet. 
Soul singer Sam Smith has released a sample of the movie’s theme song, called Writing’s on the Wall. 4 days!! http://t.co/LYGQePI8Cm Thanks to everyone pre-ordering, can't wait for you to hear 'Writing's On The Wall' https://t.co/nEYRMK8qif
